	<h2>Summary of the subcellular localization data</h2>
	
	<p align="justify">In summary ComPPI contains 269 586 major localizations for 171 559 proteins
	(no localization for 16 390 proteins). The average number of major localizations for one protein is 1.57.
	The interaction and localization score algorithm works with major localizations (detailed below).</p>
	
	<p>The final distribution of the proteins in the major localizations:
		<ul>
			<li><b>cytoplasm:</b> 75 257 proteins</li>
			<li><b>nucleus:</b> 64 385 proteins</li>
			<li><b>mitochondrion:</b> 21 373 proteins</li>
			<li><b>secretory-pathway:</b> 38 578 proteins</li>
			<li><b>membrane:</b> 50 989 proteins</li>
			<li><b>extracellular:</b> 19 004 proteins</li>
		</ul>
	</p>	
	
